1. nvm

Install nvm

Download nvm
$ git clone git://github.com/creationix/nvm.git ~/.nvm
To activate nvm, you need to source it from your bash shell
$ echo "source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh" >> .bashrc

Install version of node.js

In this example I am going to install node v0.10.15. We first need open new bash session. You can also do this by typing bash again.
$ bash
$ nvm install v0.10.15 #This takes a while.
To make the latest v0.10 branch default you do
$ nvm alias default 0.10

2. npm

Install pendencies

$ npm install
$ npm install bower (-g?)
$ bower install

3. grunt

$ npm install grunt-cli (-g?)

4. sass

$ npm install grunt-contrib-sass --save-dev

$ gem install sass

----

Notas: 

* (Tom) Tive que rodar a opção -g pro grunt e bower

* Para construir: 
$ grunt build

* Subir o aplicativo
$ python -m SimpleHTTPServer    

* Acessar o aplicativo abrindo no navegador o 0.0.0.0:8000/app/
